.TH BACKFILL_WALLETS 1 "2026-03-29" "stophammer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
backfill_wallets \- rebuild wallet endpoints, classifications, and artist links
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B backfill_wallets
[
.BI --db " PATH"
] [
.B --refresh
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B backfill_wallets
rebuilds wallet identity state from source payment-route data in four passes.
While it runs, it coordinates with
.BR resolverd
via
.BR resolver_state.backfill_active .

Default mode runs passes 1\(en4:

Pass 1 normalizes endpoint facts from all payment routes. Pass 2 creates
provisional wallets and applies hard-signal classification. Pass 3 links
same-feed artist evidence. Pass 4 removes orphaned wallet entities.

With
.BR --refresh ,
pass 5 also runs: it re-groups same-feed endpoints, re-derives display names,
generates review items for ambiguous wallets, and runs orphan cleanup.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --db " PATH"
Path to the SQLite database. Defaults to
.BR ./stophammer.db .
.TP
.B --refresh
Run pass 5 (global refresh / owner grouping) in addition to the default
passes 1\(en4.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run the default backfill:
.nf
cargo run --bin backfill_wallets -- --db ./stophammer.db
.fi
.TP
Run the full backfill including display-name refresh and review-item generation:
.nf
cargo run --bin backfill_wallets -- --db ./stophammer.db --refresh
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stophammer (1),
.BR review_wallet_identity (1),
.BR resolverd (1)
